Q1 — Easy: Word Count in a String
Problem:
Ek string di gayi hai, count karo har word kitni baar aaya hai, aur result dictionary me store karo.

Example Input:

python
Copy
Edit
text = "apple banana apple orange banana apple"
Expected Output:

python
Copy
Edit
{'apple': 3, 'banana': 2, 'orange': 1}


Q2 — Medium: Merge Two Dictionaries by Adding Values
Problem:
Do dictionaries di gayi hain jisme keys same bhi ho sakti hain. Keys ke values ko add karke ek new dictionary banao.

Example Input:

python
Copy
Edit
dict1 = {'a': 10, 'b': 20, 'c': 30}
dict2 = {'a': 5, 'b': 15, 'd': 25}
Expected Output:

python
Copy
Edit
{'a': 15, 'b': 35, 'c': 30, 'd': 25}


Q3 — Tricky: Nested Dictionary Value Update
Problem:
Ek nested dictionary di gayi hai jisme student ka naam aur unka marks stored hai. Tumhe ek specific student ke marks update karne hain.

Example Input:

python
Copy
Edit
students = {
    '101': {'name': 'Ashu', 'marks': 85},
    '102': {'name': 'Ravi', 'marks': 78}
}
Task: Ravi ke marks ko 90 karna.

Expected Output:

python
Copy
Edit
{
    '101': {'name': 'Ashu', 'marks': 85},
    '102': {'name': 'Ravi', 'marks': 90}
}


Q4 — Advanced: Group Employees by Department
Problem:
Ek list of dictionaries di gayi hai jisme har employee ka naam aur department diya hai. Tumhe department ko key banake employees ki list value me store karni hai.

Example Input:

python
Copy
Edit
employees = [
    {'name': 'Alice', 'dept': 'IT'},
    {'name': 'Bob', 'dept': 'HR'},
    {'name': 'Charlie', 'dept': 'IT'},
    {'name': 'David', 'dept': 'Finance'},
    {'name': 'Eve', 'dept': 'HR'}
]
Expected Output:

python
Copy
Edit
{
    'IT': ['Alice', 'Charlie'],
    'HR': ['Bob', 'Eve'],
    'Finance': ['David']
}
